(43, 9, 18, 43, 5, 44, 44, 'did not believe concerning him', 'Belief and Honor in Context', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and the challenge of seeking validation from others rather than from God. In both passages, the emphasis on belief is central, with the Jews'' disbelief in the blind man''s healing paralleling the idea that seeking honor from one another undermines true faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
